<%= content_for(:head) do %>
  <script type="text/javascript">
  $(function(){
    $('body').addClass('inaug');
    $('.form-container').toggle();
    $('.join').click(function(){
      $('.form-container').toggle();
      $('#actions').toggle();
    });
  })
  </script>
<% end %>
<div class="row">
  <div id="home_signup" class="span7 center">
    <div id="form_header">
      <h1 class="old">Be a part of the solution</h1>
    </div>
    <div class="form-container">
    <%= render 'new_user_form' %>
    </div>
    <div id="actions">
      <%= link_to "auth/twitter", :id => "twitter_oauth" do %>
        <%= image_tag("twitter-logo.png") %><p>Sign up with Twitter</p>
      <% end %>
      OR
      <%= link_to "Sign up with Email", "#", :class => 'home-action btn join', :id => "email_signup" %>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
<div class="row">
  <div class="step span4">
    <div class="interior">
      <h2>Step 1: Sign Up</h3>
      <p>Sign up using your Twitter account, or create one with us. Either way works and will get you started in no time.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="step span4">
    <div class="interior">
      <h2>Step 2: Add a problem</h3>
      <p>Have an opinion on what the Government is doing? Want to complain or gripe? Feel free. There's just one caveat: every problem must come with a solution. Is this an idealistic approach? You bet.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="step span4">
    <div class="interior">
      <h2>Step 3: Discuss others' problems</h3>
      <p></p>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>